Sovereign Trust Insurance Plc has reassured Nigerians of improved services using technology to drive its operations in the nation’s insurance landscape. The Deputy General Manager- Corporate Communication and Investor Relations, Segun Bankole, at the yearly open forum and thanksgiving breakfast retreat held in Lagos, urged members of staff to double down their efforts to ensure that customers are satisfied. “We owe customers the obligation to serve them better than ever so that they can keep coming back as we are in business because of them,” Bankole said. He stressed that the company would continually do all within its powers to ensure that the staff is constantly exposed to the best of human capacity development training both within and outside the country to expand the professional horizon of the workforce and engender quality and better service delivery.  He also encouraged the personnel to personally develop themselves at every given opportunity they have. “We are indeed appreciative and look forward to your continued patronage and support in 2023. Be rest assured of our avowed commitment to providing top-notch professional risk advisory services at all times you throw the opportunity our way. We look forward to making your 2023 a memorable, rewarding and fruitful one,” he assured customers. 